{{unref|date=February 2011}}

In some forms of [[football]], a '''cavalry charge''' is a (now forbidden) tactic where, as one player runs forwards with the ball, his team-mates charge in rank forwards behind him: see [http://www.irblaws.com/downloads/EN/law_10_en.pdf Section 10.4(o) of the Laws of Rugby Union].

